  <td>The map is divided into squares using a grid. Each square has a x and y cooridnate. All the tiles in one square, that have the same x and y coordinates, are called a tile stack. In other words, all tiles that are stacked on top of each other are a stack.
  <td>TileStack - This is a pointer to an entire stack (cannot be converted to a TileXY)
  <td>TileXY - This is the (x,y) location of a tile stack (can be easily converted to a TileStack)
